    "This is primarily because several issues in NL requirements, e.g., incompleteness and ambiguity, make it challenging to automate automated test artefact generation [9], [22].",
    "Hence, most of these existing approaches use templated requirements or some form of formalism [9], [25], [28].",
    "Furthermore, test scenarios that are used in several organizations, including Austrian Post, are only seldom the format of test artefacts automatically generated from requirements.",
    "Very few research works have addressed this problem.",
    "For instance, Sarmiento et al. [29] utilize Petri-Nets to transform NL requirements into test scenarios."
